value.0: *fixes you with the steadiest of gazes* Aye?

Did she now... *opens the satchel and examines various parcels of food and equipment*

Typical o' the lass, she does like thae city too much fer a ranger an no' mistake. Ah well. She promised we'd pay ye, ah'd guess?
Fair be fair. Here's yer coin. Mayhap Nevyth'll stop chasin tavern tail an' come huntin' fer proper quarry again, some day soon..

Hunters, by trade. Niall, Finian, and Aisling. We've what remains of our quarry 'ere for sale if you're interested *gestures to the carcasses and animal skins around you*. And supplies for your own ventures if no.

*smiles languidly and gestures the forest* No one stopping ya. In fact, if you can bring us back any decent sized deer, we'll do the dirty work and chop 'em up for ya. We don't need the meat, we'll give ye that back. So long as we can keep a few choice bits for ourselves. How's that sound?

Eh? It be meat, <lad/lass>. If'n ye cannot prepare it yerself ye can take it to the butcher in the village. Or the butchers in Corwell, if ye don't mind city folk.. Either way, they be givin ye some coin fer it I would think.

Hmm... *rubs his chin and looks appraisingly at you* We 'ave our own special places o' course. But if yer lookin fer safe huntin grounds, free o' wolves an such like, ye best travel due south-east o' this area we stand in now. Don't go straight south nor straight east, ye ken? Just south-east ((he gestures towards the south-east corner of the area))

That way there be a part o' the Dafyd Heights which be blessed by Earthmother herself. Ye won't even find pesky wolves nippin' at ye there, 'tis a sanctuary. Just mind ye don't go rampagin' an killin' everythin ye see without a care... if'n ye disturb the Mother's balance, bad times for ye an no mistkae.

Aye, the Heights. If'n it be a clear day ye can see the ridgeline itself from where we stand now, above the Llyrath forest away south o' here.

The rest o' the Heights have no' too much dangers, if'n ye can handle the odd wolf wantin' te take a bite outta ye *grins wolfishly*.

Just watch that ye dinnae run head-first inta any o' them bloody troglodyte beasts. Sometimes they be comin down from their cave on the south side o' the ridge. Nasty lizard buggers. They'll cut ye up real good if'n yer not careful.

By the Mother, ye ask many questions... *scratches his chin* The Llyrath be the forest that runs all the way across the south o' Gwynneth. Ye can see the treeline from here, can ye no?  Just south o' where we stand. It be a great forest indeed... runs east ta west, down past Pontswain an Mannan's Scar west o' Corwell, even te Kimball Moor. Long way *nods sagely*

Like ah said, <lad/lass>, it be fair safe up around Dafyd Heights. But away from the slopes o' the Heights, there be bandits that camp out in the woods... an' if'n ye go anywhere west o' the Heights within the Llyrath, ye'd best be mighty brave or mighty foolish... much o' Llyrath be right dangerous these days.
Blimey... aright then
*nods, eyeing you* Mayhap we'll bump into you when we cut open the next great bear or wolf. This aint easy work, ye ken? Forest's full of dangers. You'd do well to watch your back...
Fine piece of work. Here. *takes the deer, skins, dresses and butchers it, then hands back much of the meat and a dried hide he's fetched*
I have these hunting supplies your friend Nevyth asked me to deliver to you *hand over the satchel*
Yes she did, and let me tell you, that satchel is heavy and it's a LONG way from Corwell to... wherever this is. Where's my payment?
Thanks. I'd like to have a look at what you're selling.
Thanks. I'd like to ask you some questions about hunting please
Thanks *leave*
Must have taken a wrong turn somewhere, sorry.
Are you selling anything?
Who're you?
I see. Farewell.
What would you think of a little competition, hunting wise?
What am I meant to do with the meat you give me back, then?
Where's the best place to hunt?
What's to the south-east that's so special then?
What about the rest of these.. Dafyd Heights was it you called them?
What's the Llyrath Forest?
Is it dangerous?
I have more questions about hunting.
Where's the best place to hunt again?
Thanks, I'll keep that in mind *leave*
Thanks for the advice. *leave*
Sounds like a deal. I'll see you again soon, no doubt.
*lugging a dead deer* Here on business.
Meat, thank you kindly. *hands over the deer*
Hide, if you please. *hands over the deer*
